cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a generative model neural network approach for outlier detection and signal recovery, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses optimization techniques such as ADMM and gradient descent, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
